<subSubSection id="0BD92BDAE0C33038187C447E1C5A01C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="habit and habitat">
<paragraph id="A049C85E8F28390E997822DA8D1B7CBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Habit and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="36EA36443AB0D6C9D7D089F09632F15A" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Scattered to gregarious on the branch in mixed forest dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="02A5B866D7BE5AE24B5CDA77993EC148" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Camellia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Camellia japonica" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="3C844C2AE5605E7ED99E07516E2580EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Camellia japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Linne, in summer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
