<subSubSection id="BBCCE655711D79D39B920AA6EB0D81DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="88A2E2B6459A7A736E1EC1A551976A55" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED5C23DB1F0017ABFF952D5B30FC5F8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="4CF49C73C56FDB8587CCCF0EE47E607D" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis albicantipes" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albicantipes">
<emphasis id="111A6A26C8551E392F73257BB34973CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis albicantipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A0EDDCB0106B1D1AF6476B4026AFBF7F" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. ramulicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="ramulicola">
<emphasis id="ECA212921B454DEE171FF6E80B68E985" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. ramulicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="245D46340A3DF056545A436E55B06E5C" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. koreana" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="koreana">
<emphasis id="68A089EAA58ADA7C9A4C3477F6F3A96A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. koreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when comparing macro-morphological characteristics. 
<taxonomicName id="2C36428C34D1647EC0F6BD246A15CDFC" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="T. H. Li &amp; S. F. Deng" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis ramulicola" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ramulicola">
<emphasis id="42EAB5E06CC96930A5912410D921C344" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis ramulicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="D48B911173F338D5C699D753693D90CF" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. albicantipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="albicantipes">
<emphasis id="122AA0621E22413B5A7CFCC2F2094F68" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. albicantipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a reddish pileus, fewer and buff lamellulae (1-4), a shorter and thinner stipe (12-23 
<normalizedToken id="A4592FE5731DEC18133418F23E045902" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm), shorter and slightly elongated basidiospores (6.6-8.4 
<normalizedToken id="E2D37542C864E153BECD3C493B21D389" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken id="B260DE41DC72C478E20F76BBC38B4C69" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), shorter basidia (23-27 
<normalizedToken id="F7C3B604AF2D23BCE663BC755DC7996C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.8-5.5 
<normalizedToken id="6F0370DEE8907DC8F6F13E18E9F9DB81" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), and shorter cheilocystidia (23-27 
<normalizedToken id="03DD770D7C8DA6831DC33314A0D2E3C7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-6 
<normalizedToken id="EE0349E1388C8D0D83CB257A4AAB8010" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="556D44C2251C15F346411C91C1A1628D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" author="Deng, SF" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="663 - 670" refId="B6" refString="Deng, SF, Li, TH, Jiang, ZD, Song, B, 2016. Gymnopus ramulicola sp. nov., a pinkish species from southern China. Mycotaxon 131 (3): 663 - 670, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" title="Gymnopus ramulicola sp. nov., a pinkish species from southern China." url="https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" volume="131" year="2016">Deng et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E961C2F83453AC97D3965F9F8091DC34" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Antonin, Ryoo &amp; H. D. Shin" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis koreana" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="koreana">
<emphasis id="B060CF515E71F417F63B8F58668B8FE3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis koreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="45130BEF53AA85CC89581AA67CDFF37E" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. albicantipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="albicantipes">
<emphasis id="CA797E7CC84040F1E346930C4DB03504" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. albicantipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a larger pileus (27-60 mm), more lamellae (15-20) and lamellulae (2-3), longer and thicker stipe (14-70 
<normalizedToken id="806A953D972E5FD9264245D2F3894184" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="733F529B693BF126700CD4C87718492F" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), bigger and elongated basidiospores (7.5-10 
<normalizedToken id="105ADDFB1CD08B548A14DFA8DDC987A9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 
<normalizedToken id="1236C062AE3919C4E1DE6401AAB2A612" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), cheilocystidia with different shapes and sizes (25-55 
<normalizedToken id="35CBFEE4981BA84D59A86DF3E7D68028" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-10 
<normalizedToken id="77D4F04F6AC3C074D1EAEBFAF4ECB01F" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), and incrustation dark brown in KOH (
<bibRefCitation id="773405CE05980F7D0085BFC4F5E9F9D2" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5248/112.189" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="189 - 199" refId="B3" refString="Antonin, V, Ryoo, R, Shin, HD, 2010. Two new marasmielloid fungi widely distributed in the Republic of Korea. Mycotaxon 112 (1): 189 - 199, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5248/112.189" title="Two new marasmielloid fungi widely distributed in the Republic of Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.5248/112.189" volume="112" year="2010">
<normalizedToken id="B655F6EC0CD018DF400DC231DAD62E84" originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
